Richarlison scored a crucial second-half winner as Everton beat Chelsea to move within two points of the Premier League safety zone. The Brazilian was gifted the chance as Cesar Azpilicueta dallied on the ball, allowing him to steal in and finish calmly.   Qatar World Cup: The cost of Nigeria’s failure     Basketball prodigy Okunbo tipped to rule basketball world     NBB of C holds ceremonial pullout for Alaafin   Chelsea’s Mason Mount hit both posts with a 20-yard strike before Everton keeper Jordan Pickford brilliantly kept out Azpilicueta’s follow-up shot. The win moves the Toffees to within two points of Burnley in 16th and Leeds in 17th, with a game in hand on both.   BBC sport